								<div class="title" id="post-title-2238647">
																		
															</div>
				<div class="info">
					<span class="printuser avatarhover"><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/silberescher" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(304355); return false;"  ><img class="small" src="http://www.wikidot.com/avatar.php?userid=304355&amp;amp;size=small&amp;amp;timestamp=1610250857" alt="Silberescher" style="background-image:url(http://www.wikidot.com/userkarma.php?u=304355)"/></a><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/silberescher" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(304355); return false;" >Silberescher</a></span> <span class="odate time_1424738962 format_%25e%20%25b%20%25Y%2C%20%25H%3A%25M%7Cagohover">24 Feb 2015 00:49</span>
														</div>
			</div>
			<div class="content" id="post-content-2238647">
									

<p>Two pieces, connected as part of a larger storyline.</p>
<p>Thanks to all the people who helped with Sanctuary, and to Decibelle, TwistedGears, Randomini, Vince, and everyone else who pitched in help with the writing and design for The Beginning of the End.</p>
<p>For a hint if you're stuck in The Beginning Of The End:</p>
<div class="collapsible-block">
<div class="collapsible-block-folded"><a class="collapsible-block-link" href="javascript:;">Spoiler</a></div>
<div class="collapsible-block-unfolded" style="display:none">
<div class="collapsible-block-unfolded-link"><a class="collapsible-block-link" href="javascript:;">Necessary&nbsp;to&nbsp;see&nbsp;the&nbsp;real&nbsp;story</a></div>
<div class="collapsible-block-content">
<p>You need to get the bureaucrat rank &quot;The Pawn&quot; to see the real ending. All other ranks lead to a &quot;failure state&quot;, essentially, including both approving everything and denying everything.</p>
</div>
</div>
</div>
<p>A list of what is reimagined:</p>
<div class="collapsible-block">
<div class="collapsible-block-folded"><a class="collapsible-block-link" href="javascript:;">Spoiler</a></div>
<div class="collapsible-block-unfolded" style="display:none">
<div class="collapsible-block-unfolded-link"><a class="collapsible-block-link" href="javascript:;">–&nbsp;hide&nbsp;block</a></div>
<div class="collapsible-block-content">
<p>Primary characters:<br />
<a href="/scp-343">SCP-343</a><br />
<a href="/scp-732">SCP-732</a></p>
<p>Secondary is MTF Omega-7, including<br />
<a href="/scp-076">SCP-076</a><br />
<a href="/scp-105">SCP-105</a><br />
<a href="/scp-079">SCP-079</a></p>
<p>Several other SCPs are mentioned, but their roles are too minor to count as a proper reimagining.</p>
</div>
</div>
</div>
<p>An explanation of some of the notation in 343's pidgin logic-English:</p>
<div class="collapsible-block">
<div class="collapsible-block-folded"><a class="collapsible-block-link" href="javascript:;">Spoiler?</a></div>
<div class="collapsible-block-unfolded" style="display:none">
<div class="collapsible-block-unfolded-link"><a class="collapsible-block-link" href="javascript:;">–&nbsp;hide&nbsp;block</a></div>
<div class="collapsible-block-content">
<p>&quot;~&quot; is &quot;the negation of&quot; or &quot;not&quot;<br />
&quot;:=&quot; means &quot;is defined as&quot;<br />
&quot;:&quot; and &quot;::&quot; form analogies: &quot;X is to Y as A is to B&quot;<br />
&quot;v&quot; means &quot;or&quot;<br />
&quot;P&quot; is the proposition at hand<br />
&quot;→&quot; means &quot;if, then&quot;<br />
&quot;↔&quot; means &quot;if and only if, then&quot;<br />
&quot;∃&quot; means &quot;there exists&quot;; &quot;∃!&quot; means &quot;there exists exactly one&quot;<br />
&quot;⊕&quot; means &quot;mutually exclusive&quot;<br />
&quot;⊤&quot; means &quot;is necessarily true&quot;</p>
</div>
</div>
</div>
<p>EDIT: In the interest of giving credit where credit's due, the CSS theme I used here is a derivative of the &quot;Hypercane&quot; style featured <a href="http://www.glorioustrainwrecks.com/node/5163">here</a>.</p>

							</div>

								
